    "title": "Lead Instructional Designer at Oxford University Press India",
    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Oxford University Press India. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Instructional Designer to strengthen our Vijayawada-based team.\n\nAbout Oxford University Press India:\nOxford University Press India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Conduct doubt-clearing sessions and remedial classes for weak students\n• Design formative and summative assessments aligned to learning objectives\n• Maintain classroom discipline and create a positive learning environment\n• Participate in teacher training and professional development programs\n• Maintain student records and prepare progress reports\n• Conduct parent-teacher meetings and update parents on student performance\n• Monitor student progress and provide timely feedback\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Data Analysis\n• Proficiency in Pedagogy\n• Proficiency in LMS Platforms\n• Proficiency in Mentoring\n• Proficiency in Communication Skills\n• Proficiency in IB Curriculum\n• Proficiency in MS Office\n• Proficiency in Research Skills\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Oxford University Press India!",
